The paper deals with the toughness of Delaunay triangulations, which is a fundamental concept in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of matchings, which falls under the scope of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The proof technique used in the paper involves analyzing the connectivity of the Delaunay triangulation, which is related to the study of graphs and networks, and hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GR (Graph Theory) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of combinatorial arguments, which is a common theme in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
